{"lemma":"صَدِيقَةٍ","slug":"صَدِيقَةٍ","root":"ص.د.ق","root_slug":"ص-د-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-د-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَدِيق","root":"صدق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24012","n24014","n24015"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"friend","examples":[{"text":"اَلصَّدِيقُ قَبْلَ الطَّرِيقْ.","english":"A friend before the road."},{"text":"Al-Shafi’iyy\nجَزَى اللّٰهُ الشَّدَائِدَ كُلَّ خَيْرٍ / وَإِنْ كَانَتْ تُغَصِّصُنِي بِرِيقِي / وَمَا شُكْرِي لَهَا حَمْدًا وَلٰكِن / عَرَفْتُ بِهَا عَدُوِّي مِنْ صَدِيقِي\njazā llāhu š-šadāʔida kulla ḵayrin / waʔin kānat tuḡaṣṣiṣunī birīqī / wamā šukrī lahā ḥamdan walākin / ʕaraftu bihā ʕaduwwī min ṣadīqī\nMay God reward my hardships,\nAlthough they make me choke.\nI thank them, but not to praise,\nFor now, through them, I know","english":"My partner and my foe."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"always truthful, veracious","examples":[{"text":"حَدَّثَنَا عُثْمَانُ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا جَرِيرٌ، عَنْ مَنْصُورٍ، عَنْ أَبِي وَائِلٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ —رَضِيَ اللَّهُ عَنْهُ— عَنِ النَّبِيِّ —صَلَّى اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ— قَالَ: «إِنَّ الصِّدْقَ يَهْدِي إِلَى الْبِرِّ، وَإِنَّ الْبِرَّ يَهْدِي إِلَى الْجَنَّةِ، وَإِنَّ الرَّجُلَ لَيَصْدُقُ حَتَّى يَكُونَ صِدِّيقًا، وَإِنَّ الْكَذِبَ يَهْدِي إِلَى الْفُجُورِ، وَإِنَّ الْفُجُورَ يَهْدِي إِلَى النَّارِ، وَإِنَّ الرَّجُلَ لَيَكْذِبُ، حَتَّى يُكْتَبَ عِنْدَ اللَّهِ كَذَّابًا»."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sˤa.diːq/","/sˤid.diːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24012","headword_ar":"صَدِيقٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A friend:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, friend:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, TA:) applied likewise to a female, (S, M, O, Msb, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqapN","text_ar":"صَدِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) the former anomalous, the latter regular; (MF;) and to a pl. number, (S, M, O, K,) as in the Kur xxvi. 101 (M) [and in several other instances, of which see one in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawiY~N","text_ar":"رَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: its proper pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSodiqaA='u","text_ar":"اَصْدِقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SudaqaA='u","text_ar":"صُدَقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SudoqaAnN","text_ar":"صُدْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) the last on the authority of Fr, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAdiqu","text_ar":"اَصَادِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, O, K,) which is a pl. pl., (K,) said by IDrd to be anomalous, unless it be a pl. pl.: (O:) and the dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suday~iqN","text_ar":"صُدَيِّقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Suday~iqiY","text_ar":"هُوَ صُدَيِّقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the most special,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most distinguished, of my friends,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of my true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere, friends."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","S","M","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n24014","headword_ar":"صُدَيِّقٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadiyqN","text_ar":"صَدِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24015","headword_ar":"صِدِّيقٌ","root":"Sdq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who speaks, says, utters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tells, truth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"truly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veraciously, much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, K:) [or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the quality of speaking, saying, uttering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"telling, truth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"truly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veraciously, in a very high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very eminent, degree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] it has a more intensive signification than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaduwqN","text_ar":"صَدُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSad~iqN","text_ar":"مُصَدِّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which may have the latter of the two meanings expl. above, or may mean one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who accepts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admits, the truth of what is said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who verifies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSad~iq","text_ar":"مُصَدِّق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eminent, degree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is added that] the fem. as used in the Kur v. 79 means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superlative in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~idoq","text_ar":"الصِّدْق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aSodiyq","text_ar":"التَّصْدِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as a possessive epithet, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu taSodiyqK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ تَصْدِيقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^imu Alt~aSodiyqi","text_ar":"دَايِمُ التَّصْدِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"always"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSad~iq","text_ar":"مُصَدِّق"},{"kind":"text","text":"in one or another or all of the senses assigned to this word above: it may be correctly rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"always, veracious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"always, accepting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confirming, the truth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and it may mean one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who verifies his saying by deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) it is said in the “ Mufradát ” [of Er-Rághib] that it has the first of the meanings expl. in this paragraph: or rather means, one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who never lies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or rather, one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by whom lying cannot be practised because of his habitual veracity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or rather, one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is true in his saying and his belief, and who confirms his truth by his deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","O","K","TA","M","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}